  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "hardhat version: 2.9.1;\r\n\r\nIssue:\r\nsolidity compiler fails to compile flattened contract with error `Multiple SPDX license identifiers found in source file`.\r\n\r\nReason:\r\nif you import multiple contracts that have an SPDX licence identifier the solidity compiler will fail to compile with the same error provided above.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/security/ReentrancyGuardUpgradeable.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/IERC721.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts-upgradeable/token/ERC721/utils/ERC721HolderUpgradeable.sol\";\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC20/IERC20.sol\";\r\n\r\nall above contracts have: \r\n`// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT` comment at the first line.\r\n\r\nSuggestion:\r\nRemove all `// SPDX-License-Identifier` comments by default when using the hardhat flatten command \r\n\r\n",
